APPETISER
Slices of seasoned tomato, rounds of marinated New Zealand fella
cheese and slices of avocado, napped with a pink capsicum
mayonnaise. Enjoy this with a glass of Chardonnay or Pinot Noir.
MAIN COURSE
An Orient-inspired sauce of cinnamon and orange makes an
interesting plate-mate for panfried lamb cutlets, crunchy
croquelles of almond potatoes and Chinese stir-fried vegelables.
A glass of Merlot will drink nicely with this dish.
Delicate parcels of salmon, filled with sevruga caviar, shallots,
chives and paprika, are seared then napped with a Champagne
sauce scented with fresh lavender petals. Accompanied by new
potatoes and chives, vichy carrots and snow peas. Champagne
is an obvious choice, but a glass of Chardonnay will offer
more comblexity
Plump pillows of ravioli filled with a savoury chicken mixture,
are blanched then lossed in hot oil with basil and chives and
served with a fresh-lasting lomato, basil sauce and a mushroon
and white wine sauce. This is enjoyable with either a glass of
Chardonnay or an oaked Sauvignon Blanc.
DESSERT
Pastry tart layered with a langy apricot puree and a rich
almond paste, topped with flaked almonds and baked until
golden. Served with sauce Anglaise. Treat yourself to a glass
of dessert wine with this dessert.
